The paper discusses the use of machine learning models, specifically neural network classifiers, in various applications such as natural language processing, computer vision, and cybersecurity. It focuses on the issue of adversarial examples and proposes a defense mechanism using Generative Adversarial Nets (GANs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
